==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Phthalimide
<hw>Phthal"i*mide</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Phthal</ets>ic + <ets>imide</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>An imido derivative of phthalic acid, obtained as a white
crystalline substance, <chform>C6H4.(CO)2NH</chform>, which has itself
(like succinimide) acid properties, and forms a series of salts. Cf.
<cref>Imido acid</cref>, under <er>Imido</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Phthalin</ent>⟦br⟧
